@MartinC  I agree with @RickBullotta . A robust UNS architecture will be agnostic to the plethora of devices on the market. It's best to assume that no device will do all you want and instead include some sort of device gateway in the system so you don't have to worry about aligning different groups in the business (such as the controls team) with the UNS development.

Check out this list for some ideas
https://matthewgea.github.io/iiot/

I favour having two pieces of hardware, independently running software that is monitoring each other in  a Active/Passive manner over have a HA Cluster, I go into details here( https://discord.com/channels/738470295056416930/740336189449699408/1215395592168149142)
but essentially if you have HA, it normally takes a few minutes to failover and sometimes not all services restart and that can take manual intervention to fix. You can lose a lot of data in 10 minutes.

